ect will directly contribute to two strategic areas: a) fostering social capital development to improve lives through education, health and nutrition; and b) strengthening institution for quality of spending and inclusive service delivery. A level two restructuring was approved on March 5, 2012 to increase the allocation available for the Recipient-Executed Trust Fund (RETF) from US_ 15.7 million to US_ 20.0 million; and include operating costs, as an eligible expenditure in the financing and grant agreements.'},PROJECT_NAME:'Health Sector Strategic Plan Support Additional Financing',PROJECTDOCS:{__DOCDATE_DOCTYPE_DOCTYPEDESC_DOCURL_ENTITYID:{DOCTYPEDESC:'Integrated Safeguards Data Sheet (ISDS),  Vol.1 of 1',DOCTYPE:'ISDS',ENTITYID:'000001843_20130131115925',DOCURL:'http://www-wds.worldbank.org/servlet/WDSServlet?pcont=details&eid=000001843_20130131115925',DOCDATE:'28-JAN-2013'},__DOCDATE_DOCTYPE_DOCTYPEDESC_DOCURL_ENTITYID:{DOCTYPEDESC:'Project Paper (PJPR),  Vol.1 of 1',DOCTYPE:'PJPR',ENTITYID:'000356161_20130219124103',DOCURL:'http://www-wds.worldbank.org/servlet/WDSServlet?pcont=details&eid=000356161_20130219124103',DOCDATE:'24-JAN-2013'}},PROJECTFINANCIALTYPE:'OTHER',PROJECTSTATUSDISPLAY:'Active',REGIONNAME:'East Asia and Pacific',SECTOR:{__NAME:{NAME:'Health'},__NAME:{NAME:'Public administration- Health'}},SECTOR1:{NAME:'Health',PERCENT:69},SECTOR2:{NAME:'Public administration- Health',PERCENT:31},SECTOR_NAMECODE:{__CODE_NAME:{NAME:'Health',CODE:'JA'},__CODE_NAME:{NAME:'Public administration- Health',CODE:'BQ'}},SECTORCODE:'BQ,JA',SOURCE:'IBRD',STATUS:'Active',SUPPLEMENTPROJECTFLG:'Y',THEME1:{NAME:'Health system performance',PERCENT:66},THEME_NAMECODE:{__CODE_NAME:{NAME:'Health system performance',CODE:'67'},__CODE_NAME:{NAME:'Public expenditure, financial management and procurement',CODE:'27'}},THEMECODE:'27,67',TOTALAMT:0,TOTALCOMMAMT:17700000,URL:'http://www.worldbank.org/projects/P144520/health-sector-strategic-plan-support-additional-financing?lang=en'}},
